translate ru CampSlavePath_508c29f8:
    # "The guards had brought her straight to the auction stage, just as instructed."
    ""

translate ru CampSlavePath_89acfb8d:
    # "Sarah quickly realized she was not the first or even the last. There was a constant stream of new arrivals and processed slaves, flowing in and out of the square."
    ""

translate ru CampSlavePath_a191ec33:
    # "A practiced machine of human misery."
    ""

translate ru CampSlavePath_0f9f7fb3:
    # "From behind the podium, Sarah can hear the crowd growing louder. She feels the manacles cutting into her wrists."
    ""

translate ru CampSlavePath_37adaf35:
    # "One by one, she watches as the other slaves are pulled out onto the stage. Each time, a loud cheer breaks out and the sounds of bidding begin."
    ""

translate ru CampSlavePath_66509e57:
    # "It’s young, beautiful women and effeminate men who elicit the loudest cheers, and likely for the same reason, Sarah imagines."
    ""

translate ru CampSlavePath_f1078bf9:
    # "Sarah feels the chain pull, dragging her forward. She watches as the last slave, a woman only a few years older than herself, gets put at the center of the stage. Again the cheers. And the bidding. The woman keeps her head down."
    ""

translate ru CampSlavePath_2e94ee77:
    # "Sarah doesn’t want to imagine the humiliation, and yet, she knows it will soon be her turn."
    ""

translate ru CampSlavePath_954bfba4:
    # "Only two voices are left, bidding up against one another. Soon, one wins out and the woman is dragged off stage on the other side."
    ""

translate ru CampSlavePath_63b75d8e:
    # "The chain yanks, and Sarah finds herself unable to resist its pull, half stumbling onto the stage. Suddenly, the sharp sunlight make it hard for her to look out."
    ""

translate ru CampSlavePath_7afd460c:
    # "She knows the square is full. She knows it by the thunderous howling and cheering that now floods over her."
    ""

translate ru CampSlavePath_18cf125b:
    # "With her hands bound together by the manacles, she can neither cover her breasts nor her sex. She wriggles her hands in a vain attempt, but as a result pushes her breasts together."
    ""

translate ru CampSlavePath_fbc571df:
    # "The crowd only begins howling louder."
    ""

translate ru CampSlavePath_a4bde92a:
    # "Sarah tries to keep her eyes fixed to the floor, hoping to spare herself the humiliation of having to see these men."
    ""

translate ru CampSlavePath_4c6019e2:
    # "But the auctioneer won’t have it. He seizes Sarah by her chin and pulls her head up. He forces her head from left to right, eyeing across the crowd, letting everyone see what is on sale."
    ""

translate ru CampSlavePath_74ff6ffa:
    # "She spots a familiar face in the back. The old soldier. The one who had offered her food in exchange for a dance."
    ""

translate ru CampSlavePath_a95603e1:
    # "He's discussing something with the man next to him, too busy to take notice of her."
    ""

translate ru CampSlavePath_088a59cc:
    # "The bidding begins, as one voice shouts out across the other. Sarah quickly realizes she is in demand. Her eyes follow the shouting voices, seeing who it is that is trying to buy her."
    ""

translate ru CampSlavePath_83debe48:
    # "There are different faces in the crowd, but she can know these men by their gazes."
    ""

translate ru CampSlavePath_eb654c52:
    # "A great many of them have violent eyes. She almost imagines she can see their fantasies play out in their eyes."
    ""

translate ru CampSlavePath_b7df4715:
    # "With the price rising, men begin to fall off, and the bidding draws down to only about three men. A large, obese man, clad in gold, a merchant of some kind she presumes."
    ""

translate ru CampSlavePath_a7c81ad4:
    # "The other two are soldiers with the same violent eyes, she wonders if there would be any difference in which one wins her."
    ""

translate ru CampSlavePath_35618b2f:
    # "She fears all three men."
    ""

translate ru CampSlavePath_d438a638:
    # "And yet, this is what has become of her situation."
    ""

